<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1328]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,304,511,536]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">Internal.</emphasis>
Septa in 5/6–8/9 thick, muscular and funnel shaped; septa in 
<date box="[1006,1176,511,536]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317" value="2011-09-10" valueMax="2011-09-10" valueMin="2011-09-10">9/10 and 10/11</date>
thin and membranous. Two gizzards, in 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[341,355,548,573]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">5</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[409,423,548,573]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">6</emphasis>
; the latter is the largest; both gizzards are preceded by a thin-walled esophagus. Mesentery covering the esophagus of segments 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[587,601,583,608]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">7</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[665,679,583,608]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">8</emphasis>
. Lateral and dorsal lamellae large in 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1129,1197,583,608]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">11–13</emphasis>
, small in 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1323,1337,583,608]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">9</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1401,1429,583,608]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">10</emphasis>
. Coagulated blood in the body cavity in 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[635,663,620,645]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">10</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[730,755,620,645]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">11</emphasis>
. Calciferous glands absent. Intestine beginning in 17/18. Intestinal typhlosole simple, a thin line from 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[658,686,655,680]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">32</emphasis>
to 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[723,751,655,680]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">52</emphasis>
. Lateral typhlosoles absent. Intestinal caeca absent, intestine in 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[184,253,692,717]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">18–32</emphasis>
with a rough to pebbly appearance. Single dorsal vessel visible throughout. Supra-esophageal vessel visible in 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[263,333,727,752]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">10–12</emphasis>
. Lateral hearts in 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[539,580,727,752]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">6–9</emphasis>
. Latero-esophageal hearts in 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[915,985,727,752]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">10–12</emphasis>
. Ventral vessel present. Plectonephridia present, over 50 per segment (observed in segment 30).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1328]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">
Holandric. Testes in 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[428,456,799,824]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">10</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[509,534,799,824]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">11</emphasis>
, attached to iridescent male funnels by coaugulum, the latter are the largest. Two pairs of racemose seminal vesicles of similar size in 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[754,768,836,861]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">9</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[826,854,836,861]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">12</emphasis>
. Two pairs of tubulo-racemose prostates of similar size in 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[236,264,871,896]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">18</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[324,352,871,896]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">20</emphasis>
, tongue-shaped; muscular duct narrower and shorter than glandular part; central duct present, although very small and difficult to observe (
<figureCitation box="[662,731,908,933]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1884,1906]" captionTargetBox="[185,1394,201,1840]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[178,1410,193,1848]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Right prostate glands of segment 18 of the three new species. A – C. External appearance, dorsal view, photograph. D – G. Cross section, scanning electron micrographs. A, D. Zapatadrilus aurelius sp. nov. B, E. Zapatadrilus montezumensis sp. nov. C, F, G. Zapatadrilus huastecus sp. nov. In external appearance (A – C), the prostates of the three species are racemose, but internally (D – G), the cross sections reveal the presence of a single central duct; therefore the prostates are tubulo-racemose. The central duct is indicated by a red arrow. Scale bars = 100 µm (D, E), 50 µm (F), 10 µm (G)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263280/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
C, F, G). Retractor muscles in 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1076,1146,908,933]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">17–22</emphasis>
. Male ducts intraparietal. Ovaries one pair in 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[382,410,943,968]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">13</emphasis>
, arbuscular. Two pairs of spermathecae with sessile diverticulum, in 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1210,1224,943,968]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">7</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1284,1298,943,968]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">8</emphasis>
, opening to spermathecal pores in 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[409,423,980,1005]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">8</emphasis>
(the anterior ones) and 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[703,717,980,1005]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">9</emphasis>
(the posterior ones). 
<typeStatus box="[965,1069,980,1005]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">Holotype</typeStatus>
with the four spermathecae not symmetrically placed; the anterior in segment 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[674,688,1015,1040]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">7</emphasis>
(right) and 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[822,836,1015,1040]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">6</emphasis>
(left), the posterior in 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1093,1107,1015,1040]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">8</emphasis>
(right) and 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1242,1256,1015,1040]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">9</emphasis>
(left); openings to spermathecal pores in 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[438,452,1052,1077]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">8</emphasis>
(the anterior ones) and 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[727,741,1052,1077]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">9</emphasis>
(the posterior ones). A short duct continues to an ovoidal or pear-shaped ampulla, which in some cases is considerably elongated. Each spermatheca with a single sessile diverticulum with multiple chambers (
<figureCitation box="[581,647,1124,1149]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1915,1937]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,196,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1905]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Zapatadrilus huastecus sp. nov. Holotype EOL 4490. A. Anterior region of specimen, external ventral view. B, C. Right spermatheca from segment 7: dorsal view (B) and ventral view (C). D – E. Right spermatheca from segment 8: dorsal view (D) and ventral view (E). Am = Ampulla, Di = Diverticulum, Du = Duct. Gm = Genital marking, Gp = Genital papilla. Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263278/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
B–E).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="317" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1328]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1159,1184]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name 
<taxonomicName box="[464,574,1159,1184]" class="Clitellata" family="Acanthodrilidae" genus="Zapatadrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Crassiclitellata" pageId="6" pageNumber="317" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="huastecus">
<emphasis box="[464,574,1159,1184]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">huastecus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to &quot;huasteco&quot;, the gentilic adjective of the people from the Huasteca region.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="317" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1328]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1231,1256]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">Remarks.</emphasis>
Most similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[525,793,1231,1256]" class="Clitellata" family="Acanthodrilidae" genus="Zapatadrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Crassiclitellata" pageId="6" pageNumber="317" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="huastecus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[525,793,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">Zapatadrilus huastecus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[806,902,1231,1256]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[806,895,1231,1256]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is 
<taxonomicName box="[947,1074,1231,1256]" class="Clitellata" family="Acanthodrilidae" genus="Zapatadrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Crassiclitellata" pageId="6" pageNumber="317" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="aurelius" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[947,1074,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">Z. aurelius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1087,1182,1231,1256]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1087,1182,1231,1256]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
The two species are separated by body size (144–172 vs. 
<quantity box="[565,704,1268,1293]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.045" metricValueMax="1.25" metricValueMin="0.84" pageId="6" pageNumber="317" unit="mm" value="104.5" valueMax="125.0" valueMin="84.0">84–125 mm</quantity>
), the first dorsal pore (13/14 vs. 11/12) and last latero-esophageal heart (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[222,250,1303,1328]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">12</emphasis>
vs. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[295,323,1303,1328]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">13</emphasis>
). Differences between 
<taxonomicName box="[582,722,1303,1328]" class="Clitellata" family="Acanthodrilidae" genus="Zapatadrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Crassiclitellata" pageId="6" pageNumber="317" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="huastecus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[582,722,1303,1328]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">Z. huastecus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[728,817,1303,1328]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[728,817,1303,1328]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
and other species of the genus are presented in Table 1.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
